<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1419,1590]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
This species remains known from a single female that is in poor condition. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, L. A." box="[989,1151,1419,1446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" pagination="1 - 106" refId="ref5972" refString="Mound, L. A. (1974) Spore-feeding Thrips (Phlaeothripidae) from leaf-litter and dead wood in Australia. Australian Journal of Zoology, 27 (Supplement), 1 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 027" type="journal article" year="1974">Mound (1974)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[1314,1380,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Pyrgothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="faurei">
<emphasis box="[1314,1380,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">faurei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[151,257,1455,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Pyrgothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviceps">
<emphasis box="[151,257,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">breviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Haga, K." box="[370,510,1455,1482]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" pagination="263 - 280" refId="ref5835" refString="Haga, K. (1975) A revision of the genus Pyrgothrips Karny with keys to the world species (Thysanoptera, Tubulifera). Kontyu, Tokyo, 43 (3), 263 - 280." type="journal article" year="1975">Haga (1975)</bibRefCitation>
considered them to be distinct. More specimens are needed to determine the range of structural variation and decide if the two names represent different species.
</paragraph>
